{"id": "duc04-testb-48:8#25", "contents": "Qin Yongmin's case highlights the challenges faced by dissidents in China, where the code of criminal procedure guarantees the right to a defense lawyer. However, the elder Qin reported that some lawyers approached declined to take the case, while others were warned by security officials not to get involved. Qin Yongmin was arrested on November 30, just hours after his mother's death, and was not allowed to attend the funeral. His father now feels compelled to protest his treatment, despite disagreeing with his son's political tactics."}
